label.value: visceral muscle tissue

value.value: A muscle tissue that is associated with soft internal organs (viscera).
It is quite common to refer to visceral muscles as smooth muscles, by analogy with vertebrates; however, most visceral muscles in arthropods are actually striated.

label.value: visceral striated muscle tissue

value.value: A striated muscle tissue that is associated with soft internal organs (viscera).

label.value: infectious disease control objective specification

definition.value: Objective specification that is realized by processes that are able or likely to stop the spread of a disease in a population.
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/apollo-sv.owl

label.value: infectious disease control strategy

definition.value: Plan specification whose objective specification is an infectious disease control objective specification.

label.value: disease transmission model

definition.value: Algorithm that models the progress of a transmissible disease in a population.

label.value: place closure control strategy

definition.value: Infectious disease control strategy that has an action specification that is realized in closing facilities where organisms congregate during times when the facilities normally would be open.

label.value: case isolation control strategy

definition.value: Infectious disease control strategy that has an action specification that is realized in isolating organsims who are infectious.

label.value: vector control strategy

definition.value: Infectious disease control strategy that has a vector control action specification as part.
